brainly_data.question:
Macy is tutoring students in mathematics during her summer break. She charges $20 for a 30 minute session and $35 for an hour. The graph shows the number of 30 minute and 1 hour sessions she needs to have in order to make $280. 

During her first week of tutoring, she only has 1 hour sessions, but makes exactly $280. How many tutoring sessions did Macy have during the first week?
brainly_data.subject: Mathematics

all_answers.question:
Macy is tutoring students in mathematics during her summer break. She charges $20 for a 30 minute session and $35 for an hour. The graph shows the number of 30 minute and 1 hour sessions she needs to have in order to make $280. 

During her first week of tutoring, she only has 1 hour sessions, but makes exactly $280. How many tutoring sessions did Macy have during the first week?
all_answers.subject: Mathematics
all_answers.text:
Since Macy only had one hour sessions, divide the total she made by the price of the one hour session.

280 / 35 = 8 tutoring sessions
